prerequite:
1. have windows 11 pro installed ( having lower versions will not work)
2. make sure virtualization is enabled on your computer ( check youtube )
2. install wsl 2
 cmd --> run as admin -->run: wsl --install 
   if it fails to install open cmd as admin --> run:  netsh winsock reset
   then run wsl --install again.
3. then download docker desktop online and install it. everything should work smoothly 

 NB!!!
 to use minkube docker desktop must be running 
 1. powershell as admin
 2. choco install minikube (using chocolatey as the package manager)
 3. run: minikube start --driver=docker
 4. run: minikube config set driver docker (to make docker the default driver)


 
